dataIdInfo.idPurp: Existing (2019) bike facilities in the San Diego Region. This dataset was developed for the primary purpose of updating the SANDAG San Diego Regional Bike Map and the interactive bike map on the iCommute website.
dataIdInfo.idAbs: This dataset uses the SanGIS Roads_All layer as the basis for the linear features. SANDAG obtained input on bike network data from local jurisdictions in 2019 and used this information to update the regional bikeways dataset. For specific information regarding the status of bike facilities represented in the data, please contact bike planning staff for the respective local jurisdictions. This dataset is available for viewing in an interactive web map. Visit 511sd.com/bikemap to view the interactive map.

overview.eaover: This dataset is a spatial representation of San Diego County's bicycle network based on San Diego County road network data. Significant attribute fields in this dataset are the RD20FULL, ROUTE, and Jurisdiction fields. RD20FULL represents the road linear features and corresponding names based on the SanGIS Roads_All layer. ROUTE signifies the linear features for the bicycle network, as defined by class (see ROUTE attribute details for information on the bicycle classes). The Jurisdiction field delineates which jurisdiction each bike segment falls within.
overview.eadetcit: Information on bicycle facility classifications is available from the Highway Design Manual at: http://www.dot.ca.gov/hq/oppd/hdm/pdf/english/chp1000.pdf
